Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a red-brown pottery vessel, the interior is slightly grooved and partially spotted with a dark-brown resinous deposit, the exterior is covered with a red-brown slip and remains of one line of black-painted Greek text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393857) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393857)
